ke clamp.","Handlebar","Pinch bolts","Top yoke clamp","Alignment mark","Tighten the yoke clamp pinch bolts in the sequence that follows to ","8 Nm",":","Outside bolt","Inside bolt","Outside bolt again","Inside bolt again.","Position the front brake master cylinder.","Fit the clamp with the \"UP\" marking upwards and install the fixings. Align the master cylinder with the handlebar alignment mark.","Clamp","Fixings","\"UP\" arrow","Top yoke removed for clarity","Master cylinder alignment mark","Master cylinder clamp","Master cylinder","Top yoke alignment mark","Tighten the clamp fixings, upper one first, to ","12 Nm",".","Position the right handlebar switch housing onto the right handlebar. Align the locating pin on the switch housing with the hole in the handlebar.","Install the fixings that attach the right switch housing to the handlebar and tighten to ","2 Nm",".","Fixings","Right hand switch housing","Install the fixing that attaches the front brake switch and bracket to the front master cylinder. Tighten the fixing to ","2 Nm",".","Fixings","Right hand switch housing","Route the harness for the right handlebar switch housing through the headstock cable guide.","Route the switch harness as shown below, and connect the electrical connector to the main harness.","Right handlebar switch harness","Electrical connector, 8-way","Main Harness","Fit the rubber band that holds the right handlebar switch harness, throttle sensor harness and the front brake hose together at the headstock.","Left Handlebar Installation","Install the left handlebar into the top yoke clamp.","Align the handlebar alignment mark with the front corner of the split in the yoke clamp.","Handlebar","Pinch bolts","Top yoke clamp","Alignment mark","Tighten the yoke clamp pinch bolts in the sequence that follows to ","8 Nm",":","Outside bolt","Inside bolt","Outside bolt again","Inside bolt again.","Position the clutch lever assembly onto the handlebar.","Install the clamp and the two fixings. Do not tighten at this stage.","Align the clutch lever split line with the alignment mark on the handlebar. Tighten the clamp fixings, upper one first, to ","12 Nm",".","Fixings","Clutch lever clamp","Alignment mark","Align the left switch housing to the handlebar. Make sure that the locating pin aligns with the hole in the handlebar. Fit the two screws and tighten to ","2 Nm",".","Left handlebar switch housing","Fixings","Position the clutch switch onto the clutch lever.","Install the fixing and tighten to ","2 Nm",".","Clutch lever","Clutch switch","Fixing","Route the harness for the left handlebar switch housing through the headstock cable guide.","Route the harness through the retention features on the left harness retention moulding, as shown below.","Connect the two electrical connectors for the left handlebar switch housing to the main harness.","Left handlebar switch harness","Electrical connector, 6-way","Electrical connector, 13-way","Main harness","Fit the rubber band, as noted during disassembly, to hold the handlebar and ignition switch harnesses and the clutch cable together.","Install the left hand grip with two fixings and washers, and tighten to ","3 Nm",".","Fixing (one of two shown)","Perform the following operations:","Twist Grip - Installation","Handlebar End Weights - Installation"," (if applicable)","Fairings - Installation","Battery - Installation","Seat - Installation"],"viewCount":0,"infoType":"InfoType08","createdAt":"2024-04-18T13:07:59.014Z","updatedAt":"2024-04-18T13:07:59.014Z","__v":0}